                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/622.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Consul <persName type="to">Alger</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 290.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 617
                    of May 22, 1915, in regard to the protest made by you against the expropriation
                    of the water plant at Mazatlan.</p>
                <p>The Department approves the course pursued by you in this matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
